text: Eau Claire is a cool town. I went there with a few buddies that were from there when I lived in St. Paul.
There were lots of cool towns like that actually. Appleton, Wausau and eagle river(I think?) were all a fun time.
It's a nice place, but man is it whitey whitepeopleville.
It's the midwest though so that's just kinda what happens
At least it's not Milwaukee segregated too Dana
Yeah, Milwaukee it's intentional. Here there's just not many non-white people.

Unrelated note: there's a new dorm that just opened up a couple blocks from my office, and the park where there college kids get into the river to go tubing is a few blocks in the other direction. My co-worker who bikes to work just left for the day and wound up riding his bike into a lamp post staring at like 30 girls in bikinis walking down to the park with tubes from the dorm. He wants me to give him a lift to Walgreens to get an ace bandage since he thinks he sprained his ankle. I told him he had to wait long enough to me to tell someone about his idiocy.
Bahahahahaha, if you are going to look, slow down and stop, find a place that makes it look like you're resting
That's wonderful
Not for your buddy but for everyone else
Got his ankle wrapped and hauled him and his bike home, the jackass.
Finally decided to read Ready Player One since the movie isn't far off. I'm sure it'll be good since Speilberg, but man is the book super masturbatory, and the prose is kinda terrible
Yeah, that's one I've stayed away from for that exact reason. Even though like everyone I know loves it.
It's a fast read so far, i'm maybe a quarter way through in an hour, and it's interesting enough. Just poorly written all around
Thats good that it's easy and interesting. But I guess it just sounds like too much 80s for me.
Way to much, lol. And it's kinda bullshit how much flack Stephanie Meyer gets for being a hack -which she is- but Cline gets a bit of a pass, He's every bit as mockable as a writer
Lol, that's an unpopular opinion I've been waiting to hear
Not just for the prose, either. He's doing the same utterly unaware teenage studyhall daydream wish fulfillment as her.
Keep going. It gets literally masturbatory.
And, yeah, is there a name for when your theme is your Mary Sue?
It easy to cry sexism, but when he gets Speilberg to direct his fanfic and Meyer gets the director of the Nativity Story . . .
To be clear that's not to say Meyer isn't a terrible writer. She's awful. I just couldn't help but immediately compare the two.
